A rape case was opened shortly after the Thursday attack and the 30-year-old man was apprehended earlier on Friday. CAPE TOWN A man has been arrested for allegedly raping his neighbour s 13-year-old daughter in Ngqamakhwe in the Eastern Cape.The suspect allegedly accosted and sexually assaulted the victim on Thursday, at his home in the Nqileni location.The child is believed to have been placed in his care, after her mother went to Johannesburg.The police s Jackson Manatha says: This young girl went to the suspect to request a book so that she can read and prepare for examinations. She was never given the book, instead she was accosted and raped by the suspect. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)